        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-18T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-18T19:00:00-05:00" n="1407" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1407">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394A.1115/11–1849</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Macdonald</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-18T19:00:00-05:00">November 18, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>471. View issuance evac warnings Amcits Formosa and special concern for welfare
                    dependents, Dept unable justify travel additional <pb facs="1368" n="1358" xml:id="pg_1358"/> dependents Formosa at this time. Dept therefore refusing
                    passports all dependents, official and nonofficial, desiring proceed Formosa and
                    discouraging such travel persons already in possession passports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
